Vehicular movement at the Lagos Ibadan Expressway has been restored as men of the anti riot unit of Nigeria Police Force have moved into the area and have now cleared the road and movement on both sides of the expressway has resumed, However many of the road users had discontinued their journey after being told that the rioters blockade stretched to Ibadan and Sagamu Meanwhile Several anti riot police vehicles and officers are now manning and patrolling the road to prevent further breakdown of law and order More to comeâ€¦